---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms that govern your access to and use of the Equity Guardians website and your general relationship with Equity Guardians."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of Service"
    description="The terms that govern your use of this Site and your general relationship with Equity Guardians."
  />

  <section>
    <div class="container legal-wrap">
      <div class="legal-meta reveal">
        <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> July 4, 2026 <span class="sep">·</span> <strong>Last updated:</strong> July 6, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <article class="legal-body reveal">
        <p>
          Please read these Terms of Service (the &ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) carefully. They govern your
          access to and use of <a href="https://www.equityguardians.com">www.equityguardians.com</a>
          (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;) and your general relationship with Equity Guardians LLC
          (&ldquo;Equity Guardians,&rdquo; &ldquo;EG,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or
          &ldquo;our&rdquo;). By using the Site, you agree to these Terms and to our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the Site.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Who We Are; What We Do</h2>
        <p>
          Equity Guardians is a home-equity protection service for homeowners. We are not a law
          firm and do not provide legal advice, and we are not a real estate brokerage. The Program
          is delivered through independently licensed attorneys, licensed real estate professionals,
          and an EG case manager who coordinates. EG itself does not practice law or perform real
          estate brokerage services.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Relationship to the Program Agreements</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms govern use of the Site and general matters between you and EG. The Equity
          Guardians program (the &ldquo;Program&rdquo;) itself is governed by separate written
          agreements, the Member Service Agreement (for homeowners) and the Partner Realtor
          Services Agreement (for real estate professionals). If these Terms conflict with one of
          those agreements as to its subject matter, that agreement controls for the parties to it.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>You must be at least 18 years old and located in the United States to use the Site and the Program.</p>

        <h2>4. No Legal Advice; No Attorney-Client Relationship</h2>
        <p>
          Information on the Site and provided by EG is general in nature and is not legal advice.
          EG is not a law firm. Using the Site or the Program does not create an attorney-client
          relationship with EG or the case manager. Legal advice and representation are provided
          only by independent, licensed attorneys under a separate engagement between you and the
          attorney.
        </p>

        <h2>5. No Real Estate Brokerage by EG</h2>
        <p>
          EG does not perform real estate brokerage services. All real estate brokerage activity is
          performed by licensed real estate professionals acting within their license.
        </p>

        <h2>6. No Guarantee of Results</h2>
        <p>
          EG and the attorneys, real estate professionals, and partners in its network cannot and
          do not guarantee any particular result. Without limitation, we do not guarantee that a
          foreclosure will be prevented or postponed, that a loan will be modified or refinanced,
          that a home will sell at any particular price or time, that any specific savings or
          equity will be achieved, or any particular outcome for a homeowner or Partner Realtor.
          Past outcomes do not predict future results.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Third-Party Providers</h2>
        <p>
          The attorneys, real estate professionals, and savings and cashback partners involved in
          the Program are independent third parties. EG coordinates the Program but is not
          responsible for the acts, omissions, advice, or services of these independent providers,
          except as expressly stated in the applicable Program agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Acceptable Use of the Site</h2>
        <p>
          We grant you a limited, revocable, non-exclusive license to access and use the Site for
          your own lawful, personal, non-commercial purposes. You agree not to use the Site
          unlawfully; interfere with or disrupt it; attempt to gain unauthorized access; collect or
          harvest data; infringe others&rsquo; rights; or misrepresent your identity or affiliation.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          The Site and its content, and the Equity Guardians name, logo, and brand elements, are
          owned by EG or its licensors and are protected by law. We grant you a limited license to
          view the Site for the purposes above. You may not use our marks or content without our
          prior written permission.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Your Submissions; Electronic Communications</h2>
        <p>
          Information you submit through the Site is handled as described in our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. You consent to receive communications from us
          electronically, and you agree that electronic records and signatures are valid and
          enforceable under the federal E-SIGN Act and applicable state law.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Disclaimers</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Site and all information and services are
          provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available,&rdquo; without warranties of any
          kind, whether express or implied, including implied warranties of merchantability,
          fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, EG will not be liable for any indirect,
          incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for lost profits or lost
          business, arising out of or relating to the Site or these Terms. Nothing in these Terms
          limits any liability that cannot be limited under applicable law, including rights under
          applicable consumer-protection statutes.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, you agree to indemnify and hold harmless EG and
          its officers, employees, and agents from third-party claims, losses, and reasonable
          expenses (including reasonable attorneys&rsquo; fees) arising out of your misuse of the
          Site or your violation of these Terms or applicable law.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Consumer Protection; No Waiver</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing in these Terms waives, or is intended to waive, any right or remedy you have
          under applicable consumer-protection law that cannot be waived.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will revise the &ldquo;Last
          updated&rdquo; date above. Your continued use of the Site after changes take effect means
          you accept the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>16. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We may suspend or terminate your access to the Site if you violate these Terms or
          applicable law. Your participation in the Program is governed by the applicable Program
          agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>17. Miscellaneous</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms, together with the Privacy Policy, are the entire agreement between you and
          EG regarding your use of the Site. If any provision is held unenforceable, the rest
          remains in effect. Our failure to enforce a provision is not a waiver. You may not
          assign these Terms without our consent; we may assign them to an affiliate or successor.
          Neither party is liable for delays or failures caused by events beyond its reasonable
          control.
        </p>

        <h2>18. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Equity Guardians LLC<br />
          1 World Trade Center, 85th Floor, New York, NY 10007<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:admin@equityguardians.com">admin@equityguardians.com</a><br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+18889540999">(888) 954-0999</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-wrap {
    max-width: 780px;
    padding-block: 3rem 5rem;
  }
  .legal-meta {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #FBF7EE;
    border: 1px solid #E9DEC1;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--slate-700);
  }
  .legal-meta p { margin: 0; }
  .legal-meta .sep { color: var(--teal-500); margin: 0 0.35rem; }
  .legal-body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--slate-700);
  }
  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--navy-900);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .legal-body p { margin: 0 0 1.1rem; }
  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .legal-body li { margin-bottom: 0.55rem; }
  .legal-body a { color: var(--teal-700); text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal-body a:hover { color: var(--teal-500); }
  .legal-body strong { color: var(--navy-900); }
</style>
